' ========== Inheritance Relationships ==========
Permission <|-- RollerPermission : extends
RollerPermission <|-- GlobalPermission : extends
RollerPermission <|-- ObjectPermission : extends
ObjectPermission <|-- WeblogPermission : extends

' ========== Implementation Relationships ==========
UserManager <|.. JPAUserManagerImpl : implements

' ========== Composition/Aggregation ==========
JPAUserManagerImpl *-- JPAPersistenceStrategy : uses

' ========== Association Relationships ==========
User "1" -- "*" UserRole : has roles >
User "1" -- "*" WeblogPermission : has permissions >
Weblog "1" -- "*" WeblogPermission : grants permissions >
Weblog "*" -- "1" User : owned by <

' ========== Dependency Relationships ==========
GlobalPermission ..> User : references
WeblogPermission ..> User : references
WeblogPermission ..> Weblog : references
JPAUserManagerImpl ..> WeblogPermission : manages
JPAUserManagerImpl ..> UserRole : manages
JPAUserManagerImpl ..> GlobalPermission : creates

' ========== Notes ==========
note right of GlobalPermission
  **Global Permission Hierarchy:**
  ┌─────────┐
  │  ADMIN  │ ← implies all below
  ├─────────┤
  │  WEBLOG │ ← implies LOGIN
  ├─────────┤
  │  LOGIN  │ ← base permission
  └─────────┘
end note

note right of WeblogPermission
  **Weblog Permission Hierarchy:**
  ┌────────────┐
  │   ADMIN    │ ← full weblog admin
  ├────────────┤
  │    POST    │ ← can publish posts
  ├────────────┤
  │ EDIT_DRAFT │ ← can create drafts
  └────────────┘
end note

note bottom of JPAUserManagerImpl
  **LLM Analysis - Design Issues:**
  • SRP Violation: 631 lines of code
  • Handles User, Permission, and Role operations
  
  **Suggested Refactoring:**
  Split into:
  1. JPAUserCrudManager
  2. JPAPermissionManager  
  3. JPARoleManager
end note

note left of RollerPermission
  **Template Method Pattern:**
  Defines skeleton of permission
  operations. Subclasses implement:
  • setActions()
  • getActions()
  • implies()
end note

